  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston writes about the experiences of Warren Weston in England. He arrived on the Great Western. She relates Warren&apos;s conversations with Joshua Bates pertaining to family affairs. When Mr. Bates &quot;did not see how we lived on $500 a year,&quot; Warren failed to tell him that &quot;the rest of the means was raised by ourselves.&quot; Mr. Bates has transferred a ship to Warren at a low price to be paid in installments,--&quot;the same thing as a gift.&quot; Mr. Bates did not mention Warren&apos;s engagement directly, but talked of the folly of too early marriages.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">There are two layers of writing, lengthwise and crosswise, throughout this letter.</subfield>
  </datafield>
